<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    Block the "Ship to the Stars" endgame quest.

    That is the vanilla EndGame_ShipEscape QuestScriptDef (its name rule renders as "Ship to the
    Stars"): the friendly-AI "start a hidden starship and fly off this rimworld" journey offer. It's
    isRootSpecial (its GiveQuest_EndGame_ShipEscape incident has baseChance 0), so it never comes from
    the random-quest roll - it is fired solely by a StorytellerCompProperties_SingleOnceFixed comp on
    the shared abstract BaseStoryteller, 20 days in. Removing that comp (patches run before def
    inheritance resolves, so it propagates to every storyteller, The Antagonist included) suppresses
    the quest. All other shared base comps are left intact.

    Global by nature (no storyteller offers it), not scoped to The Antagonist - the comp is inherited
    from the base def and can't be removed for one storyteller only.
-->
<Patch>
    <Operation Class="PatchOperationRemove">
        <xpath>Defs/StorytellerDef[@Name="BaseStoryteller"]/comps/li[incident="GiveQuest_EndGame_ShipEscape"]</xpath>
    </Operation>
</Patch>
